.TH NORND 8 "2026" "norn @PACKAGE_VERSION@" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
nornd \- norn node daemon: cluster KV host and IPC server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nornd
.RB [ \-\-identity
.IR PATH ]
.RB [ \-\-socket
.IR PATH ]
.RB [ \-\-class
.IR CLASS ]
.RB [ \-\-data\-dir
.IR PATH ]
.RB [ \-\-foreground ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nornd
is the reference node daemon built on
.BR libnorn (3).
One process owns the event loop: it runs a norn node, hosts a replica of the
fleet's Raft-replicated key-value store, and serves local tools (the
.BR norn (1)
CLI and applications) over a Unix-domain socket.
.PP
A node's identity is its
.B Ed25519 SSH key.
The daemon signs norn handshakes with that key directly, so the key never has
to be re-encoded and an ssh-agent-held key can be used without exposing it. A
system instance defaults to the host key
.RI ( /etc/ssh/ssh_host_ed25519_key );
a per-user instance defaults to
.IR ~/.ssh/id_ed25519 .
.PP
The daemon exposes three distinct key-value surfaces:
.IP \(bu 3
the
.B cluster KV
\(em small values replicated by Raft across the fleet (also holds the
SSH/GPG key directory);
.IP \(bu 3
the
.B node-served KV
\(em a node's own values streamed directly to a peer on request (unbounded
size); and
.IP \(bu 3
.B BEP-44
DHT records (public, size-limited).
.PP
On gaining leadership the daemon publishes its own SSH public key into the
cluster key directory under
.IR peer/<nodeid>/ssh .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-identity " " \fIPATH\fP
OpenSSH Ed25519 private key file to use as the node identity. Default
.I ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
(user) or the host key (system unit).
.TP
.BR \-\-socket " " \fIPATH\fP
Unix socket to listen on. Default
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/nornd.sock
or
.IR ~/.norn/nornd.sock .
Ignored when the socket is passed in by socket activation.
.TP
.BR \-\-class " " \fICLASS\fP
Node class:
.BR server ,
.BR workstation ,
.BR laptop ,
or
.BR mobile .
Only
.B server
nodes with proven uptime are eligible to lead the cluster; the others join as
learners so a mostly-offline edge fleet never stalls writes. Default
.BR server .
.TP
.BR \-\-data\-dir " " \fIPATH\fP
State directory (reserved for node-served content and snapshots).
.TP
.B \-\-foreground
Do not detach. The daemon already runs in the foreground; this flag is
accepted for
.B Type=notify
service units.
.SH SOCKET ACTIVATION
.B nornd
supports systemd and launchd socket activation. When a listening descriptor is
handed over via
.B LISTEN_FDS
(with a matching
.BR LISTEN_PID ),
the daemon uses it instead of binding its own socket and does not unlink it on
exit. For
.B Type=notify
units it sends
.B READY=1
to
.B NOTIFY_SOCKET
once it is serving (no libsystemd dependency).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
Base directory for the default socket path.
.TP
.B HOME
Used to resolve the default identity and socket when
.B XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
is unset.
.TP
.BR LISTEN_FDS ", " LISTEN_PID
Socket-activation handover (systemd/launchd).
.TP
.B NOTIFY_SOCKET
Readiness notification socket for
.BR Type=notify .
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /run/nornd/nornd.sock
System-instance IPC socket (per the shipped unit).
.TP
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/nornd.sock
User-instance IPC socket.
.TP
.IR /etc/ssh/ssh_host_ed25519_key ", " ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
Default node identities (system / user).
.TP
.IR @prefix@/lib/systemd/system/nornd.{socket,service} ", " @prefix@/lib/systemd/user/nornd.{socket,service}
Installed systemd units.
.TP
.I @prefix@/lib/launchd/io.norn.nornd*.plist
Installed launchd plists.
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.BR SIGINT ", " SIGTERM
Graceful shutdown: stop serving, and unlink the socket unless it was
socket-activated.
.SH EXAMPLES
Run a user instance against your SSH key:
.PP
.RS
.EX
$ nornd --identity ~/.ssh/id_ed25519 --class workstation
$ norn cluster status
role: leader
members: 1
.EE
.RE
.PP
Enable the socket-activated user service:
.PP
.RS
.EX
$ systemctl --user enable --now nornd.socket
.EE
.RE
.PP
Enable the system service (keyed on the host SSH key):
.PP
.RS
.EX
# systemctl enable --now nornd.socket
.EE
.RE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Clean shutdown.
.TP
.B 1
Startup failure: unreadable identity, client/cluster creation failed, or the
socket could not be bound.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR norn (1),
.BR libnorn (3),
.BR systemd.socket (5),
.BR sd_notify (3)
.SH AUTHOR
The norn development team.
.SH LICENSE
MIT License. See the LICENSE file for details.
